body.prompt:
${ "App idea:
" + (.trigger.intent // "A RetroForge pixel-art sprite editor.") + "

The build target is a SINGLE-FILE static web app (index.html + style.css + app.js in /sandbox) — keep the spec achievable as one self-contained page. Write the product spec to /sandbox/SPEC.md per your instructions (Objective, User Stories, Acceptance Criteria, and the 4-dimension Design Rubric). Do not build the app; write only SPEC.md, then end with a one-line summary." }

${ "Review the RetroForge Sprite Editor the Generator built in /sandbox.

FIRST read /sandbox/SPEC.md — the Planner authored the Objective, Acceptance Criteria, and Design Rubric (the 4 dimensions) there; judge the work against it. (App idea: " + (.trigger.intent // "a retro pixel-art sprite editor") + ")" + "

Then read index.html, style.css, and app.js in /sandbox. Inspect the actual palette, tools, layout, type scale, color/contrast, and the drawing/export logic. Judge against SPEC.md’s acceptance criteria AND the four design dimensions (design_quality, originality, craft, functionality). Return ONLY the strict JSON verdict from your instructions. Be demanding: meets_criteria true ONLY for genuinely crafted, distinctive, usable work that satisfies the spec." }
